dots ignore rune type spells so if he has his epic effect on it is a waste for you to nuke :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxashrenthelost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xashren the Lost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/5/01 5:41:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling Tactics. Druid vs Wizard?</span><hr size=1> A decent Wizard will hand you your rear on a silver plate unless you can get out of range *fast* and start dropping DoTS, and then nuking while he tries to dispel.<br>
<br>
They have one spell that gives them a huge advantage over every casting class: Shock of Lightning, their level 12 lightning DD.<br>
<br>
Why? Because it is unresistable, guaranteed knockback unless you are up against a wall, or in a corner. You might resist the damage down to 40 or 50 points, but if he's geared, that adds up, slowly but surely. Typically, they just open with that, and keep hammering you with it until you die, or get so low on health that they can finish you with one of their bigger nukes, or just smack you around with one of the more powerful Lure spells, which cuts through resistances like a knife through butter.<br>
<br>
Good way to counter this unresistable knockback is to wedge yourself in to a corner, or, barring that, get up against a wall. Now the knockback does nothing, and they are pretty much wasting their mana while you nuke the hell out of them. Once they switch to their big guns, just heal yourself. Due to the PvP damage reduction, your heals will be far more efficient than his nukes, and unless your gear is very poor, he will run OOM long before you do.<br>
<br>
Now, keep in mind that wizards are fragile, very fragile, and they have to rely soley on resists, the level 12 dd, and sheer overwhelming damage to stop you. <br>
<br>
Basically, you just have to run. Run run run. Use your speed advantage. If you're in a large enough area, SoW will eventually give you enough breathing room to cast a DoT (don't waste mana on snare, they'll resist it every time with decent gear), and then go pure offense while they try to dispel. If they don't dispel, run them around and keep out of their nuke range until they die from your dots. Dead wizard.<br>
<br>
If you're in the Arena, then Levitate becomes your best friend. Scramble up those pillars. Bind on top of one before the fight if you can. Get up there, and you are usually out of their spell range, unless they are fairly high level, in which case you're going to eat an Ice Comet, or possibly something much, much more nasty.<br>
<br>
Once on the pillar, drop dots and start blasting, until they come in to spell range. Then you run again.<br>
<br>
It's all about exploiting the fact that we move faster than they do, even if they have Jboots. They stop to cast, we run away. Unless you started running when you were very close to them, you'll be out of spell range before their nukes land.<br>
<br>
All in all, Druid vs Wizard is usually either very one sided (if the wizard uses his lvl 12 DD, and druid doesn't counter it, or if the wizard doesn't use said DD at all, in which case he's toast), or it's a very long and involved fight that usually drains both casters nearly dry, and often comes down to who has the larger mana pool and better resists.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarkinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkinia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/5/01 6:12:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.antilogic.net/leet_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling Tactics. Druid vs Wizard?</span><hr size=1> How lame is it to just run away...face them like a man, or dont face them at all, running around and kiting is lame.<br>
<br>
A wizard has Very few HP.  PvP DD does not do 100% and is less mana effiecant than healing...Did any of you compete or watch the bobt?  How long did the ones who straight nuked last? about 1 round max. <br>
 I wrote this thinking you were 50+, but some applies to all lvls i guess, so take it for what its worth:<br>
<br>
Your Nukes will take mana and will not be nearly as efficiant as doting, but remeber a wizard has low HP.  Best damage/mana ratio is Winged Death with right click Arms, because they are almost NEVER resisted even with 255 MR.  1 Winged death, traped under 2 crap buffs and your garenteed the winner if you can heal yourself.  Ro's, dot arms, then winged death, and the nasty DoT is very hard to dispell.<br>
<br>
Winged death does about 1k dmg in pvp, thats a large portion of a wizards HP bar.  Even if you dont think you can handle them with DoTs, or arnt of sufficent lvl to have Winged death, if they straight nuke, and you straight heal, you will have more mana in the end.  <br>
<br>
Think about it, wildfire, IF it hits for full in pVp is about 600ish damage and it rarly hits over 400 if that (with decent resists).  Thats 320 mana for 400-600 damage.  Your heal (choroblast? Didnt read what lvl you were), is 480ish HP for 175 mana.  Thats almost 1k of healing per same amount of mana as 1 of their nukes.  <br>
<br>
Even consider melee, it isnt huge, but epic is 20/30 other weapons are decent i guess, but any damage has  a chance of interupting their spell, and it does do some damage, so it cant hurt. <p>-ArK<br><br>

