<br>
The first time I fought the wizard, I tried to go toe to toe, and heal myself, couldnt get a heal off, too damn slow casting, and kept getting stunned.  I died pretty fast.  <br>
<br>
The second time, I ran a little, hit with a magic debuff first, to cancel the armor skin, or whatever it is.  Next, I snared and rooted, ran a little more.  Hit with a blind (cheap cost, but got her timing off on her spells).  Every time I heard her casting, I hauled ass out of range, kept just on the edge of range from her, when she hit me, I ran out of range and healed myself.  <br>
<br>
I would run in, hit her with something mana cheap, and run back out of casting range to heal.  Finally, I ran in, and she didnt cast, she was out of mana, dead wizard.  So basically, run the wizard out of mana, by running in and out of casting range, in casting range to take a single hit, out of casting range to heal yourself, your mana will outlast their mana this way (healing more efficient than damage).  When they stop casting when you run in, they are out of mana, and time to kill a wizard.  <br>
<br>
Judicatio Choppe 54 Monk<br>
